@Node Register "Registering NewsAgent"

@{b}Registration Information.@{ub}

	NewsAgent is ShareWare.  That means that you can copy it if you
want, and I encourage you to give this program to anybody who may find it
useful.  On the other hand, it is not cheap to develop (I have only a dial-up
account), and so if you really like it, and would like to see future versions,
then donations are encouraged.  Anybody who sends money, will automatically
get new versions, containing extra features not available to unregistered
users.

	As and extra incentive shareware version has a couple of extra
'features', which are not present in the registered version.  Firstly,
certain groups are not available.  I wont list which ones, but if the
program reports 'invalid group' when you *know* it exists, you've found
one...  Secondly, a requester will pop up now and again during downloads,
requiring you to click ok.  The registered version has no restrictions on
groups, and can download uninterrupted.

	I ask for 10 (UK) pounds as a minimum donation.  Cash is prefered, in
either UKP, US$ ($20), or DM (30).  International Money Orders (in UKP) are
also accepted.  I may be willing to take alternative payment, such as disks,
CD's etc - so if converting cash is a problem get in touch.

	Please include your EMail address when mailing your donation, as I
send out registered version and updates by EMail (its much faster and safer
all round that way).

You can send further enquiries to:

E-Mail:			NewsAgent@pyrotek.demon.co.uk

And registrations to:

Snail-Mail:		Jason G Doig,
			20 Queens Crescent,
			Kinghorn,
			Fife.        KY3 9RG

@EndNode

@Node Probs "Its all going wrong!"

@{b}Common problems.@{ub}

This section contains answers to common questions I get about NewsAgent
not working...


NewsAgent crashes!

	Well, hopefully it doesn't.  However, I can't possibly test every
	single combination of newsdownloads, button clicks and system
	configurations, so there may well be a bug left somewhere.  If
	NewsAgent crashes, make sure you follow all the advice here, and
	if it doesn't help, get in touch.


Not enough stack!

	It used to be the case that if NewsAgent ran out of stack, it
	crashed (not an unreasonable reaction).  This was slightly
	unfriendly however, and as of 1.4 it checks that it has the
	minimum stack requirement before starting.  If NewsAgent
	complains about lack of stack, then you'll need to increase it.
	From the CLI this involves typing 'stack XXXX' where XXXX is
	the amount of stack to give.  NewsAgent needs at least 16384
	bytes.  Your best bet is probably to put the line 'stack 16384'
	into 's:shell-startup'.  Running from the WB, it should run
	fine from the standard supplied icon.  If you change the icon,
	make sure you change the stack setting using the 'Information'
	option from the WBench menu 'Icons'.  If you are using some
	kind of tool-launching utility, consult its own documentation.

Can't access some groups!

	Have you @{" Registered " Link "Register"}?  Some groups aren't available if you don't!

Doesn't remember what articles I've read!

	Has the news-server's database been rebuilt recently?  The chances
	are that the articles have been renumbered and that NewsAgent is
	a little confused.  Edit the group file (usually
	UULIB:NewsAgentGroups), and delete the number after each group name.
	NewsAgent will assume you haven't read the group before, and update
	the information next time you read the group.

@EndNode

